# CODEOWNERS for admin/push permission preservation
# Set admin(s) as code owner for .github/settings.yml to help enforce permission boundaries
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/repository-ownership-and-permissions/about-code-owners
#
# This is intended for use with branch protection on the 'main' branch.

# Critical configuration files requiring admin approval
.github/settings.yaml @tdorsey
.github/CODEOWNERS @tdorsey

# Security-related documentation and policies
SECURITY.md @tdorsey

# Label configuration (SECURITY SENSITIVE)
.github/labels/labels.yml @tdorsey

# Global fallback - repository owner is responsible for all files
* @tdorsey
